1
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:32,530
史前巨鳄

2
00:02:48,900 --> 00:02:53,250
替海獭贴标签真的有钱赚吗
They actually pay you for this, to tag beaver?

3
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:54,710
你猜
Imagine.

4
00:02:56,330 --> 00:02:58,000
你在讽刺我吗
Was that, like, sarcastic?

5
00:02:58,620 --> 00:03:02,430
你们渔猎局都瞧不起乡下警长
'Cause I know what you Fish and Game guys think of county sheriffs.

6
00:03:02,460 --> 00:03:06,430
老爱说些刺耳的话
We know you like to give these one-word, sarcastic answers.

7
00:03:06,460 --> 00:03:07,640
是啊
Gee.

8
00:03:09,710 --> 00:03:10,520
你问我
You ask me,

9
00:03:10,550 --> 00:03:13,400
动物干什么是它们的事
what an animal does in the wild is his own business.

10
00:03:13,430 --> 00:03:16,230
只要不要影响人类就行
So long as he doesn't do it to man.

11
00:03:17,640 --> 00:03:19,860
我想这句话是马克吐温说的
I think Mark Twain said that.

12
00:03:19,890 --> 00:03:21,820
我想不是吧
Yeah, I think he didn't.

13
00:03:21,850 --> 00:03:25,200
不过既然是你说的就算是吧
But since you said it, I guess we're covered.

14
00:03:42,660 --> 00:03:45,550
这些人说话都带刺
Everyone's a comedian, sarcastic.

15
00:05:07,290 --> 00:05:08,680
# I'm sleepin'

16
00:05:08,710 --> 00:05:11,180
# And right in the middle of a good dream #

17
00:05:11,210 --> 00:05:13,180
# And all at once I wake up #

18
00:05:13,210 --> 00:05:17,060
# From something that keeps knocking at my brain #

19
00:05:17,090 --> 00:05:19,020
# Before I go insane #

20
00:05:19,050 --> 00:05:21,940
# I hold my pillow to my head... #

21
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:56,890
Aah! Aah!

22
00:05:59,550 --> 00:06:01,650
# So what am I so afraid of?. #

23
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:04,150
# I'm afraid that I'm not sure of... #

24
00:06:04,180 --> 00:06:05,610
救命
Help!

25
00:06:09,270 --> 00:06:11,240
# I think I love you #

26
00:06:11,270 --> 00:06:14,360
# Isn't that what life is made of?. #

27
00:06:15,690 --> 00:06:17,080
啊
Aah ha!

28
00:06:49,180 --> 00:06:51,280
别松手
Ohh! Don't let go!

29
00:06:51,310 --> 00:06:52,740
噢 不
Oh ho ho!

30
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:57,700
啊
Aah!

31
00:07:07,910 --> 00:07:09,920
我的天呀
Aw, Jesus Christ.

32
00:07:27,550 --> 00:07:28,770
凯莉
Kelly?

33
00:07:30,470 --> 00:07:31,530
柯文
Hey, Kevin.

34
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:32,610
嗨
Hi.

35
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:35,950
我能跟你谈谈吗
Listen, uh, could I steal you for a minute?

36
00:07:46,570 --> 00:07:48,380
你在做什么?
What are you doing?

37
00:07:48,410 --> 00:07:49,960
我在静坐
Heavy breathing, meditating.

38
00:07:49,990 --> 00:07:50,970
静坐?
Meditating?

39
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:53,260
对 为了减轻压力
Yes. To relieve stress.

40
00:07:53,290 --> 00:07:55,930
你教我要靠呼吸放松
Remember, Myra, you're the one who taught me all about breathing.

41
00:07:55,960 --> 00:07:58,470
干嘛呀? 你在生小孩吗
Yes, but you're doing Lamaze. are you giving birth?

42
00:07:58,500 --> 00:08:01,180
深呼吸才能放松心情
If you're upset, long, deep breaths.

43
00:08:05,300 --> 00:08:06,400
我被柯文甩掉
Kevin dumped me.

44
00:08:06,430 --> 00:08:08,230
我知道了
I know.

45
00:08:10,100 --> 00:08:11,440
他跟你说的?
He told you?

46
00:08:11,470 --> 00:08:15,440
我有第一手消息
Well, I sort of had, uh, inside information.

47
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:21,330
你?
You?

48
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:22,710
那是在你之前
It started before you, Kelly.

49
00:08:22,740 --> 00:08:23,710
我绝对不会...
I never would have--

50
00:08:23,740 --> 00:08:24,420
你?
You?

51
00:08:24,450 --> 00:08:27,170
那只是一夜情 而且我们觉得这事就这么过去了
It was just a quick thing that we thought was over,

52
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:30,050
结果却没有
and...it's not over.

53
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:32,090
你跟柯文
You and Kevin.

54
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:34,920
我该怎么说
I--l wish I could say something to...

55
00:08:36,460 --> 00:08:38,970
人都要随心所欲
the heart wants what the heart wants.

56
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:44,250
"缅因州渔猎局长"

57
00:08:50,970 --> 00:08:52,150
基奥警长
Sheriff Keough?

58
00:08:52,180 --> 00:08:53,190
是
Yeah.

59
00:08:53,220 --> 00:08:55,860
我是渔猎局的杰克·威尔斯
Fish and Game. Jack Wells.

60
00:08:55,890 --> 00:08:57,700
最近会有熊出来伤人吗
Any recent bear attacks?

61
00:08:57,730 --> 00:08:59,030
没有
This was no bear.

62
00:08:59,060 --> 00:09:01,080
熊不会在水底吃人
Bears don't attack people underwater.

63
00:09:01,110 --> 00:09:03,910
也许是一只食人海獭
Probably a beaver, then.

64
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:07,910
你真是尖酸刻薄
Ah, a whole sentence sarcastic.

65
00:09:17,580 --> 00:09:19,680
他被咬成一半?
That the way he came out of the water?

66
00:09:19,710 --> 00:09:21,180
嗯
Yeah.

67
00:09:34,850 --> 00:09:35,690
嘿
Hey.

68
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:38,160
柯文 近来如何? 怎么样
Hey, Kevin, what's going on? What's happening?

69
00:09:38,190 --> 00:09:40,120
你的家人好吗?
How's it goin'? How's your family? Good?

70
00:09:40,150 --> 00:09:41,950
棒呆了 幸会
It's great. So nice to see you.

71
00:09:41,980 --> 00:09:43,080
快给我滚
Fuck off.

72
00:09:43,110 --> 00:09:44,580
这是公事
This is business.

73
00:09:44,610 --> 00:09:46,790
缅因州出了意外
There was an accident in Maine.

74
00:09:46,820 --> 00:09:49,250
有人在湖底被咬死
Some guy got killed by something in a lake.

75
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:53,090
大概是只熊 他们找到一颗牙齿
Probably a bear, but they found a tooth.

76
00:09:53,120 --> 00:09:54,130
牙齿?
A tooth?

77
00:09:54,160 --> 00:09:55,670
只是碎片
A fragment of a tooth,

78
00:09:55,700 --> 00:09:57,970
很大一只熊的牙齿
one they say couldn't have come from any bear.

79
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:02,220
很古老自远古的恐龙
Evidently it looks prehistoric, like maybe a dinosaur.

80
00:10:02,250 --> 00:10:05,430
原来是这样 他可能是被恐龙咬死的
Oh, well, then I'm sure that that's what it was. He was killed by a dinosaur.

81
00:10:05,460 --> 00:10:07,230
还有其他事吗
Is there anything else?

82
00:10:07,260 --> 00:10:09,640
我派你去调查
I, uh, want you to go there.

83
00:10:10,220 --> 00:10:11,440
什么?
What?

84
00:10:11,470 --> 00:10:16,110
也许是空穴来风 不过这是古生物学家的工作
It's probably nothing, but you're a paleontologist. This is what we do.

85
00:10:16,140 --> 00:10:17,490
你这是什么意思
What do you mean, this is what we do?

86
00:10:17,520 --> 00:10:19,490
我要你查明真相
I'd like you to check out this tooth.

87
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:21,320
我不是田野调查员
I'm not a field person.

88
00:10:21,350 --> 00:10:23,870
这次我希望你去
Well, on this one, I would like you to be.

89
00:10:23,900 --> 00:10:28,030
你要我去缅因州看一颗牙
You want me to go to Maine to look at a tooth?

90
00:10:29,490 --> 00:10:32,000
这是蜜拉的点子 对吧?
Oh, this was Myra's idea, wasn't it?

91
00:10:32,030 --> 00:10:33,790
当然
Oh, of course.

92
00:10:33,820 --> 00:10:36,420
让我离开一阵子冷静一下
Get me out of the office for a few days, wait till I cool off...

93
00:10:36,450 --> 00:10:37,920
不是这样的
it has nothing to do with that.

94
00:10:37,950 --> 00:10:40,550
我不做调查 也不去缅因州
I don't do field work, and even if I did, Maine?

95
00:10:40,580 --> 00:10:41,840
我对树木会过敏
I'm allergic to timber.

96
00:10:41,870 --> 00:10:43,850
- 凯莉 - 我不去缅因州
- Kelly. - I am not going to Maine.

97
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:46,390
我死也不去
I'm not going to Maine.

98
00:10:46,420 --> 00:10:48,260
想都别想
It's ridiculous.

99
00:10:54,180 --> 00:10:57,030
飞越山头会有点颠簸
It's gonna be rough as we go over these mountains.

100
00:10:57,060 --> 00:10:58,990
没关系 谢谢你
Yeah, that's fine. Thank you.

101
00:10:59,020 --> 00:11:01,150
我只想说一声
We're doing the best we can.

102
00:11:03,480 --> 00:11:05,910
别跟我说话
Could you not talk to me?

103
00:11:05,940 --> 00:11:07,200
谢谢你
Thank you.

104
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:18,210
他狂叫着就扑上来
Just came up screaming.

105
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:19,380
他说了些什么
What did he say?

106
00:11:19,410 --> 00:11:22,130
他只咽了一口气就挂了
Just kind of gurgled. He was pretty much dead.

107
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:23,890
你什么都没看到
You didn't see anything?

108
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:25,800
之前湖面很平静
The lake was calm until up he came.

109
00:11:25,830 --> 00:11:27,100
牙齿在里面
The tooth is in here.

110
00:11:27,130 --> 00:11:29,430
这里是停尸间
Oh, that's-- that's the morgue.

111
00:11:29,460 --> 00:11:30,640
是的
Yes.

112
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:33,980
里面有尸体吗
Well, is the dead guy in there?

113
00:11:34,010 --> 00:11:36,310
所以这里才叫做停尸间
That's where they keep them.

114
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:41,200
你要我把牙齿拿出来吗
Look...you want me to bring the tooth out here?

115
00:11:41,230 --> 00:11:42,530
不用
No.

116
00:11:42,560 --> 00:11:44,070
不
No. Let's...

117
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:45,650
你先请
After you.

118
00:11:46,770 --> 00:11:50,450
这是爬虫类 并不是化石
This is reptilian. And this is not a fossil.

119
00:11:50,780 --> 00:11:52,710
你真的是从他身上拔下来的
You really pulled this out of this guy?

120
00:11:52,740 --> 00:11:54,290
没错
Yes, I did.

121
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:56,880
我要用显微镜观察
I'll need to get a microscopic look at it.

122
00:11:56,910 --> 00:11:57,880
尽管用
There you go.

123
00:11:57,910 --> 00:11:59,080
太好了
Great.

124
00:12:02,660 --> 00:12:03,550
也许我应该看看
Maybe I should see--

125
00:12:03,580 --> 00:12:04,920
最好不要
I wouldn't.

126
00:12:06,460 --> 00:12:08,930
我又不是没看过死人
I can deal with dead men--bodies.

127
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:26,740
攻击持续多久?
How long did this attack go on for?

128
00:12:26,770 --> 00:12:29,580
几秒钟 八秒 最多十秒钟
Seconds. 8 maybe 10.

129
00:12:29,610 --> 00:12:32,540
他上来就是这样
Oh, and, uh, this is how he came up to the boat?

130
00:12:32,570 --> 00:12:33,750
是的
Yes.

131
00:12:36,740 --> 00:12:39,670
我想去看那座湖
I'd like to see this lake.

132
00:12:40,660 --> 00:12:43,510
方圆25里都没人住
Nobody lives within 25 miles of it,

133
00:12:43,540 --> 00:12:46,720
除了住湖畔的一对老夫妇
except some old couple who live right on the lake.

134
00:12:46,750 --> 00:12:50,680
学生偶尔会跑来裸泳
Teenagers trek in every once in a while to skinny-dip.

135
00:12:50,710 --> 00:12:52,680
没有人失踪过
None have disappeared.

136
00:12:52,710 --> 00:12:54,730
也没发生不寻常的事
None have spotted anything unusual.

137
00:12:54,760 --> 00:12:56,520
问过那对老夫妇了吗
Did you talk to the old couple?

138
00:12:56,550 --> 00:12:57,520
还没有
Not yet.

139
00:12:57,550 --> 00:12:59,100
我们还有什么支援
What kind of backup do we have?

140
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:00,900
我们?
We?

141
00:13:01,010 --> 00:13:01,940
怎么了
What?

142
00:13:01,970 --> 00:13:06,320
什么鬼博物馆会派人来这儿
I'm a little unclear as to why the museum would send somebody here.

143
00:13:06,350 --> 00:13:07,740
你对博物馆有意见?
You gotta thing against museums?

144
00:13:07,770 --> 00:13:09,320
我没有意见
No, I got nothing against museums.

145
00:13:09,350 --> 00:13:10,700
你有去过吗?
Ever been in one?

146
00:13:17,280 --> 00:13:18,540
那是什么
What is that?

147
00:13:18,570 --> 00:13:20,750
轻型气压式火炮枪
Lightweight forward-area air-device unit.

148
00:13:20,990 --> 00:13:24,550
只要一枪就能轰掉这怪物
Whatever's out there, one shot with this, it's dead.

149
00:13:24,580 --> 00:13:27,010
你带这玩意干嘛
Why exactly would you have that?

150
00:13:27,910 --> 00:13:29,170
天啊
God.

151
00:13:34,380 --> 00:13:37,060
有蚊子 我最恨蚊于
Mosquitoes. I gotta thing about mosquitoes.

152
00:13:37,090 --> 00:13:38,690
准备好了就走吧
If you're all set, let's go.

153
00:13:38,720 --> 00:13:39,940
救星来了
We're saved.

154
00:13:39,970 --> 00:13:44,230
纽约博物馆派人来支援我们
A museum in New York just sent us some additional backup.

155
00:13:44,260 --> 00:13:46,360
我是凯莉·斯科特
Kelly Scott.

156
00:13:46,390 --> 00:13:48,110
杰克·威尔斯
Jack Wells.

157
00:13:48,140 --> 00:13:49,320
嗨
Hi.

158
00:13:49,350 --> 00:13:51,370
是什么鬼博物馆派你来的吗
Uh, some museum sent you, huh?

159
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:53,370
你们都对博物馆不爽吗
What, are we all museum bigots in Maine?

160
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:54,830
她讲话很冲
She's rude sarcastic.

161
00:13:54,860 --> 00:13:56,660
你们俩很速配
You two should get along.

162
00:13:56,690 --> 00:13:58,670
女士 你不能跟来
I'm afraid I can't let you go with us, ma'am.

163
00:13:58,700 --> 00:13:59,920
基奥警长说可以
Sheriff Keough said I could.

164
00:13:59,950 --> 00:14:02,210
渔猎局的权力比警长大
Unfortunately, Fish and Game supersedes the sheriff.

165
00:14:02,240 --> 00:14:04,210
这是什么道理?
Why do you have to supersede? Maybe I might be of--

166
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:07,880
女士 这可不是探险之旅
Ma'am, look, this isn't some kind of fact-finding expedition.

167
00:14:07,910 --> 00:14:09,010
我知道
Yes, I know that.

168
00:14:09,040 --> 00:14:10,430
也不是远足
It's not a science trip.

169
00:14:10,460 --> 00:14:11,760
别这么傲慢 好吗
Could you be a little more condescending?

170
00:14:11,790 --> 00:14:13,760
我不是三岁小孩
'Cause I'm not real great with subtlety.

171
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:17,310
湖中有个怪物咬死人
Something in that lake killed somebody, right?

172
00:14:17,340 --> 00:14:19,350
我很感激你想帮忙
I appreciate you're trying to help.

173
00:14:19,380 --> 00:14:22,020
谢谢你带一瓶杀虫剂来
I'm really glad that you brought the raid.

174
00:14:22,050 --> 00:14:22,940
这样好多了
Now, that's better.

175
00:14:22,970 --> 00:14:24,110
女士 没用的
Ma'am, it's not gonna work--

176
00:14:24,140 --> 00:14:27,530
你再叫我女士我就告你 在今日的法律规定是可行的
If you call me "ma'am" one more time, I'll sue you, and with today's laws, it's possible.

177
00:14:27,560 --> 00:14:28,860
她很高竿
She's good.

178
00:14:30,020 --> 00:14:32,120
我不会干扰你们
Look, I won't interfere.

179
00:14:32,150 --> 00:14:34,370
要不然就叫警长逮捕我
And if I do, you've got a sheriff handy to arrest me,

180
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:37,250
也许你会觉得我让你没面子
but I understand if I threaten your Fish and Game authority--

181
00:14:37,280 --> 00:14:38,290
对不起
Excuse me.

182
00:14:38,320 --> 00:14:41,330
你们要去抓湖中怪物吗
Is it true you're going to look for some kind of monster in Black Lake?

183
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:44,460
那是个意外
Well, we're just gonna investigate an accident.

184
00:14:44,490 --> 00:14:45,590
没有怪物
There's no monster.

185
00:14:45,620 --> 00:14:47,760
个人被咬成两半
We heard a man was bit in half.

186
00:14:47,790 --> 00:14:49,130
那只是意外
Well, there was an accident.

187
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:51,970
仅此而已 不用担心
That's all. It's nothing to worry about.

188
00:14:56,590 --> 00:14:58,180
拜托
Oh, please.

189
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:02,230
走吧
All right. Let's go.

190
00:15:23,780 --> 00:15:28,260
我先生两年前就过世了
Well, my husband passed away. It's been almost 2 years now.

191
00:15:28,290 --> 00:15:30,720
警局并没有记录
My department doesn't have any record of that,

192
00:15:30,750 --> 00:15:32,430
毕太太
Mrs. Bickerman.

193
00:15:32,460 --> 00:15:36,390
很抱歉 我只是不喜欢记录
Well, I'm sorry. Incomplete records haunt me so.

194
00:15:36,420 --> 00:15:39,800
你先生的死因是什么?
What was the cause of your husband's death,ma'am, do you know?

195
00:15:41,340 --> 00:15:45,440
我们不想多管闲事 不过他是不是因为生病
We don't mean to invade your privacy, but was he ill? Was he sick?

196
00:15:45,470 --> 00:15:46,940
还是被吞掉?
Was he swallowed?

197
00:15:46,970 --> 00:15:48,020
警长
Sheriff!

198
00:15:48,050 --> 00:15:49,820
我们来此的原因是
Uh, Mrs. Bickerman, the reason we're here.

199
00:15:49,850 --> 00:15:54,360
昨天有人被湖底的动物吃掉
A man was fatally attacked yesterday by some animal in this lake.

