00:38:29,620 --> 00:38:31,220
嗯
Yeah.

592
00:38:31,250 --> 00:38:32,720
赫克托呢
Where's Hector?

593
00:38:33,630 --> 00:38:34,770
不知道
I lost track.

594
00:38:34,800 --> 00:38:36,640
我们分散开来
We went different directions.

595
00:38:43,850 --> 00:38:46,150
那边有水泡
There's some bubbles over there.

596
00:38:57,360 --> 00:38:58,870
拖上来
Pull it up.

597
00:38:58,900 --> 00:39:01,710
把他拖上来
All right. Come on. Bring him aboard.

598
00:39:01,740 --> 00:39:02,840
怎么回事
What's happened?

599
00:39:02,870 --> 00:39:03,540
快点
Come on.

600
00:39:03,570 --> 00:39:05,880
- 你们看到了? - 我看见了一个东西
- You see it? - We saw something.

601
00:39:05,910 --> 00:39:07,710
- 多大? - 闭嘴 赶紧上来
- How big is it? - Shut up and get on board.

602
00:39:07,740 --> 00:39:09,720
把声纳拉上来
We lost track of it. Burke, pull up the speaker!

603
00:39:09,750 --> 00:39:11,170
你没事吧
Are you all right?

604
00:39:24,890 --> 00:39:26,530
- 启动引擎 - 啊
- Grab him! - Aah!

605
00:39:26,560 --> 00:39:28,070
拉他上来
Pull him in!

606
00:39:28,100 --> 00:39:29,610
拉他上来
Pull him in!

607
00:39:33,230 --> 00:39:34,450
好了吗
That it?

608
00:39:34,480 --> 00:39:35,610
好了
Yeah.

609
00:39:36,730 --> 00:39:38,750
发生得太快 没有人看到
Nobody actually saw it. It happened suddenly.

610
00:39:38,780 --> 00:39:40,910
不是被船桨绞死的吗
Didn't get caught in the outboard?

611
00:39:41,740 --> 00:39:43,750
不是
It wasn't the outboard.

612
00:39:51,750 --> 00:39:54,930
叫他们尽快赶来
Tell them to get here fast, huh?

613
00:39:57,590 --> 00:39:59,640
你没事吧
You OK?

614
00:40:01,420 --> 00:40:02,930
凯莉
Kelly?

615
00:40:04,260 --> 00:40:05,600
没事
Yeah.

616
00:40:06,930 --> 00:40:08,820
谁都没看见吗
Nobody saw anything.

617
00:40:08,850 --> 00:40:10,980
没有
No.

618
00:40:11,930 --> 00:40:14,160
野生动物保护局正派人来
U.S. Wildlife's on their way.

619
00:40:14,190 --> 00:40:18,280
警方要封锁一切的消息
The police want to keep everything quiet so the press doesn't get wind of anything.

620
00:40:19,270 --> 00:40:21,790
大家都要我们...
Everybody just wants us to...

621
00:40:21,820 --> 00:40:23,790
按兵不动
"Sit tight."

622
00:40:30,330 --> 00:40:32,590
你真的没事吗
Are you...ok?

623
00:40:33,790 --> 00:40:35,470
呃...
Well...

624
00:40:35,500 --> 00:40:37,220
你知道
you know...

625
00:40:39,460 --> 00:40:40,970
真的
Yeah.

626
00:40:44,800 --> 00:40:47,020
警长 我
Well, Sheriff, I'm, uh...

627
00:40:48,300 --> 00:40:50,270
为你的手下感到遗憾
Very sorry about your deputy.

628
00:40:52,520 --> 00:40:54,690
他是个好人吗
He was a good man?

629
00:40:55,480 --> 00:40:57,030
是
Yep.

630
00:40:58,940 --> 00:41:01,250
只要有人丧命
Whenever somebody dies, I...

631
00:41:01,280 --> 00:41:05,450
我没能认识他就会感到难过
I always think that it's such a waste that I didn't know them any better.

632
00:41:06,570 --> 00:41:09,080
很遗憾你没认识
Sorry for your loss, Hector.

633
00:41:10,580 --> 00:41:12,500
我不是这个意思
Not really what I meant.

634
00:41:16,250 --> 00:41:20,220
他的头被咬掉
Head was just...bitten off.

635
00:41:21,750 --> 00:41:25,770
我以前常梦到我没有头
You know, I used to have a recurring nightmare that I was headless.

636
00:41:25,800 --> 00:41:29,310
我在地上看着无头的身体
I'd be down on the ground looking up at my body, no head,

637
00:41:29,340 --> 00:41:31,820
到处跌跌撞撞
just walking around bumping into everything.

638
00:41:31,850 --> 00:41:35,820
我父母不肯让我走屋
And my parents...wouldn't let me in the house.

639
00:41:35,850 --> 00:41:37,820
他们怕我撞坏新买的古董台灯
Because they just bought all these antique lamps,

640
00:41:37,850 --> 00:41:39,700
而且他们不希望我去打扰他们 王八蛋
and they didn't want me to knock them over, the fuckers.

641
00:41:40,610 --> 00:41:45,790
邻居小孩觉得我的头像一颗球
Then the neighborhood bullies, they'd see my round head on the ground looking like a ball,

642
00:41:45,820 --> 00:41:48,790
于是就把它当足球踢
and they'd come over, and they'd start a soccer game.

643
00:41:48,820 --> 00:41:50,290
我的头被踢来踢去
And as I was being kicked around,

644
00:41:50,320 --> 00:41:54,130
我却很高兴能跟他们一起玩
I'd actually just feel grateful for being allowed in the game.

645
00:41:57,370 --> 00:41:59,640
你觉得怎样?
What are-- what are your thoughts?

646
00:41:59,670 --> 00:42:01,760
你知道吗
You know, Hector...

647
00:42:01,790 --> 00:42:06,770
我相信你应该是个好疯子
I'm sure you're a fine person in your own mental way,

648
00:42:06,800 --> 00:42:10,980
我想你最好别跟我讲话
but I think it would be best if you and I didn't speak.

649
00:42:17,520 --> 00:42:18,950
野生动物保护局几时才来
When is U.S. Wildlife getting here?

650
00:42:18,980 --> 00:42:21,490
我还在等消息
I'm still waiting to confirm if they...

651
00:42:23,900 --> 00:42:26,450
噢 天
Oh, Jesus.

652
00:42:26,820 --> 00:42:28,790
我可以把他救下来
I--I could probably cut him down,

653
00:42:28,820 --> 00:42:34,800
不过他的表情有点古怪
but there's this odd look of mayhem on his upside-down face.

654
00:42:34,830 --> 00:42:36,470
汉克
Hank.

655
00:42:36,500 --> 00:42:37,670
什么?
Yes?

656
00:42:37,700 --> 00:42:39,710
你没事吧
Are you all right?

657
00:42:40,080 --> 00:42:41,760
可以救我下来吗
Could you cut me down?

658
00:42:41,790 --> 00:42:44,470
答应我你不能伤害我
Do you promise that you won't attempt to injure me?

659
00:42:44,500 --> 00:42:47,850
我连看都不想看你一眼
I have no interest in ever looking at you, Hector.

660
00:42:47,880 --> 00:42:49,060
好吧
Ok.

661
00:42:49,800 --> 00:42:53,900
直接把他拉下来就行
Just, uh, pull him down. It's a counterweight.

662
00:42:55,970 --> 00:42:57,320
我去拿刀子
Here. I'll get the knife.

663
00:42:57,350 --> 00:43:01,570
如果我记得有陷阱就不会让你去
If I'd remembered it was there, I never would've let you walk that way.

664
00:43:01,600 --> 00:43:04,330
没事了
All right. It's over.

665
00:43:04,360 --> 00:43:05,700
没事了 记得吗
It's over. Remember?

666
00:43:05,730 --> 00:43:07,200
你答应不伤害他
You promised not to hurt him, so...

667
00:43:07,230 --> 00:43:09,210
我说谎
I lied.

668
00:43:09,240 --> 00:43:10,670
等等 嘿
Wait. Hey! Hey!

669
00:43:10,700 --> 00:43:12,170
住手 住手
Come on! Hold up!

670
00:43:12,200 --> 00:43:13,710
你无处可逃了
Nowhere to go, my friend.

671
00:43:13,740 --> 00:43:15,960
别闹了
Now, just--come on! Knock it off!.

672
00:43:15,990 --> 00:43:17,630
快放下来
Knock it off. Put that down.

673
00:43:17,660 --> 00:43:18,750
冷静点
Just settle...

674
00:43:20,750 --> 00:43:22,800
小心
Jesus! Look out!

675
00:43:23,790 --> 00:43:26,180
哇
Whoa!

676
00:43:34,430 --> 00:43:35,650
操
Aw, shit!

677
00:43:54,870 --> 00:43:56,880
好吧
Ok.

678
00:43:56,910 --> 00:43:59,210
我承认
I admit it.

679
00:43:59,240 --> 00:44:01,380
那是只鳄鱼
It's a crocodile.

680
00:44:02,210 --> 00:44:04,300
它是印度太平洋鳄
He's an lndo-Pacific.

681
00:44:04,330 --> 00:44:07,390
鳞片是椭圆形 是亚洲鳄
Scales were oval. He's an Asian crocodile.

682
00:44:07,420 --> 00:44:10,020
它为什么会跑来这儿?
Why would he come here? It's impossible.

683
00:44:10,050 --> 00:44:12,020
亚洲 它是怎么来的?
Asia. How would he get here?

684
00:44:12,050 --> 00:44:15,480
香港有个猪头把它冲下马桶
Obviously some asshole in Hong Kong flushed him down the toilet.

685
00:44:15,510 --> 00:44:17,400
它一定有三十尺长
He was 30 feet, right? Had to be.

686
00:44:17,430 --> 00:44:20,490
幸好我带了一把大枪
Well, now maybe somebody's happy I brought my big gun.

687
00:44:20,520 --> 00:44:22,650
你要把它轰死吗
Oh you're gonna blow him away now?

688
00:44:22,680 --> 00:44:23,530
当然了
I should think so.

689
00:44:23,560 --> 00:44:24,410
用大炮把它轰死
With your cannon?

690
00:44:24,440 --> 00:44:25,870
是啊 不应该吗
Right. What, I shouldn't?

691
00:44:25,900 --> 00:44:29,120
- 它是大自然的奇迹 - 但是它很可怖
- Well, he's a miracle of nature, - but I know he's very scary.

692
00:44:29,150 --> 00:44:30,830
你才是大自然的奇迹
You're the miracle of nature.

693
00:44:30,860 --> 00:44:31,870
够了 冷静点
Guys, guys, easy, easy.

694
00:44:31,900 --> 00:44:34,080
今晚什么也不能做
We're not gonna do anything tonight.

695
00:44:34,110 --> 00:44:37,840
我不知道鳄鱼能横越大海
I never heard of a crocodile crossing an ocean.

696
00:44:37,870 --> 00:44:40,340
这是书本上的知识
Well, they conceal information like that in books.

697
00:44:40,370 --> 00:44:41,510
好了
All right, pal!

698
00:44:41,540 --> 00:44:42,840
冷静点
Hey, hey. hey-

699
00:44:42,870 --> 00:44:45,010
放开他
No, no. Let him go.

700
00:44:45,040 --> 00:44:46,600
我也受不了他
I'm sick of him, too.

701
00:44:46,630 --> 00:44:47,600
我得警告你
I do need to warn you, Sheriff.

702
00:44:47,630 --> 00:44:49,140
我家很有钱
The thing about being rich,

703
00:44:49,170 --> 00:44:51,680
我从小就被送去学空手道
my parents did have the added luxury of ditching me off at karate school

704
00:44:51,710 --> 00:44:53,730
我是棕带高手
on a regular basis, so I am a brown belt.

705
00:44:53,760 --> 00:44:56,020
尽管来吧
Go ahead. Take your best shot.

706
00:44:57,180 --> 00:44:58,230
汉克
Hank!

707
00:44:58,260 --> 00:45:00,480
他说他会空手道
He said he knew karate.

708
00:45:00,510 --> 00:45:01,440
你打他
You hit him.

709
00:45:01,470 --> 00:45:02,780
没错
I did, yeah.

710
00:45:02,810 --> 00:45:04,450
来
Here.

711
00:45:04,480 --> 00:45:06,660
他有说开始吗
Did he say "go"?

712
00:45:06,690 --> 00:45:09,240
比试前不都要先说开始吗
Aren't you supposed to say "go" in karate?

713
00:45:09,270 --> 00:45:10,580
他应该说开始的
You're supposed to say "go."

714
00:45:10,610 --> 00:45:13,210
离他远一点
Hank, just keep your distance from him.

715
00:45:13,240 --> 00:45:16,000
赫克托 回你的帐篷去
Hector, go to your tent. Cool down.

716
00:45:16,030 --> 00:45:18,040
他没有回答我
He doesn't answer my questions?

717
00:45:18,070 --> 00:45:20,380
你怎么不回答?
Why don't you answer my questions?

718
00:45:20,410 --> 00:45:22,920
要是我撞到树一定会说开始
I fall into a hole. I go up in a tree.

719
00:45:22,950 --> 00:45:24,170
我发誓 我会说开始
I swear to God, I'll say "go."

720
00:45:24,200 --> 00:45:25,220
先鞠躬再说开始
You bow, and then you say "go."

721
00:45:25,250 --> 00:45:27,050
你去死吧
As in "go fuck yourself."

722
00:45:27,080 --> 00:45:29,510
他们好像小孩子
Jesus. They're just like children.

723
00:45:29,540 --> 00:45:30,760
是啊
Yeah.

724
00:45:30,790 --> 00:45:32,270
老天
Oh, my God.

725
00:45:32,300 --> 00:45:34,390
你没事吧
Are you all right?

726
00:45:34,420 --> 00:45:35,940
我没事
Yeah, I'm all right.

727
00:45:35,970 --> 00:45:37,100
我有急救箱
I've got something for that.

728
00:45:37,130 --> 00:45:38,100
让我来弄
I can fix that.

729
00:45:38,130 --> 00:45:39,110
真的吗
Yeah?

730
00:45:39,140 --> 00:45:40,230
真的
Yeah.

731
00:45:41,850 --> 00:45:44,740
我得绑紧一点
I just gotta pull it a little tighter.

732
00:45:44,770 --> 00:45:46,070
好了
There we go.

733
00:45:46,100 --> 00:45:48,110
这是谁教你的?
Who taught you to be a nurse?

734
00:45:48,140 --> 00:45:49,910
我爸是外科医生
Father's a surgeon.

735
00:45:49,940 --> 00:45:54,120
我还会缝合 其实这样最好
I can even stitch in a pinch, which probably wouldn't be such a bad idea on this.

736
00:45:54,150 --> 00:45:55,750
不用了
Uh, no, thanks.

737
00:45:55,780 --> 00:45:57,040
好吧
Ok.

738
00:45:58,610 --> 00:46:02,380
鳄鱼跳出来你的表情好逗
You should have seen the look on your face when that croc jumped out.

739
00:46:04,290 --> 00:46:06,210
你看到熊的表情吗?
You see the look on the bear?

740
00:46:07,250 --> 00:46:09,130
就是那个表情
That was the look.

741
00:46:10,580 --> 00:46:12,010
我不知道
I don't know.

742
00:46:12,040 --> 00:46:15,930
大自然法则可能改变了那玩意真是...
The laws of nature could be changing, Jack.That thing out there, that's--

743
00:46:15,960 --> 00:46:18,520
你玩得很开心 对吧?
You're having the best time of your life, aren't you?

744
00:46:19,630 --> 00:46:21,150
什么?
What?

745
00:46:21,180 --> 00:46:22,940
有人被咬死耶
What? People have been killed.

746
00:46:22,970 --> 00:46:25,280
我并不开心
I hardly think I'm having a good time.

747
00:46:25,310 --> 00:46:27,190
你怎么能
Why would you--

748
00:46:29,140 --> 00:46:30,490
这么明显吗
Does it show?

749
00:46:35,530 --> 00:46:41,710
这是我第一次真正冒险
This is the first time I've ever actually...you know, been in the middle of anything.

750
00:46:42,660 --> 00:46:47,340
你就是想要来冒险吗?
Is that why you're here, to get in the middle of something?

751
00:46:49,750 --> 00:46:51,090
也许吧
Maybe.

752
00:46:52,790 --> 00:46:56,600
我老是读一些冒险故事而却没有...
I've always read about what's happened. I've never...

753
00:47:01,840 --> 00:47:03,940
我们应该上床了
We should go to bed.

754
00:47:04,680 --> 00:47:08,280
我是说该去休息了
I mean we should go to, uh... rest.

755
00:47:08,310 --> 00:47:11,280
各自回帐篷休息
We should go to our separate tents,

756
00:47:11,310 --> 00:47:13,740
我有一些
and--here-- get some--go.

757
00:47:14,520 --> 00:47:15,910
谢了
I got it.

758
00:47:21,610 --> 00:47:23,870
谢谢你帮我包扎伤口
Thanks for the bandage.

759
00:47:25,490 --> 00:47:27,380
晚安
Night.

760
00:47:27,410 --> 00:47:28,670
晚安
Yeah.

761
00:47:40,880 --> 00:47:43,310
迅雷不及掩耳
It doesn't even see him.

762
00:47:45,430 --> 00:47:47,610
看 它成功了
There, he got it.

763
00:47:49,810 --> 00:47:52,070
它只有一个天敌
He has one natural enemy.

764
00:47:52,100 --> 00:47:53,740
只有一个
Only one.

765
00:47:54,560 --> 00:47:55,660
人类
Man?

766
00:47:55,690 --> 00:47:56,820
人类
Man.

767
00:47:58,480 --> 00:47:59,950
你是专家
So you're the big expert.

768
00:47:59,980 --> 00:48:02,790
这玩意是变种吗
You think ours is some kind of mutant or---

769
00:48:02,820 --> 00:48:05,630
不一定 印度也有三十尺巨鳄
Not necessarily. There's a 30-footer in India.

770
00:48:05,660 --> 00:48:09,050
被猎杀最大的记录是27尺
Biggest one ever killed on record was 27 feet.

771
00:48:09,080 --> 00:48:11,800
它为什么跑来这里?
So why is he here?

772
00:48:11,830 --> 00:48:14,010
老实说
Honestly...

773
00:48:17,710 --> 00:48:19,430
我不知道
I don't know.

774
00:48:41,570 --> 00:48:43,460
要提高警觉
Keep your eyes peeled.

775
00:48:43,490 --> 00:48:46,380
鳄鱼的动作是很快
You know how fast these things can be.

776
00:48:46,410 --> 00:48:48,420
我身上有虱子
I've got ticks, I know it.

777
00:48:48,450 --> 00:48:51,630
虱子特别喜欢我
They're just so drawn to me. I gotta thing about ticks.

778
00:48:51,660 --> 00:48:56,300
钻进我的头发和皮肤里
Crawling up your pant leg. Put their heads under your skin.

779
00:48:57,080 --> 00:48:58,680
你们看
Look.

780
00:48:58,710 --> 00:48:59,720
什么?
What?

781
00:48:59,750 --> 00:49:01,010
杰克
Jack.

782
00:49:09,010 --> 00:49:11,360
好大的足印
That's a pretty big print.

783
00:49:19,150 --> 00:49:20,410
你飞得越来越低
Seems like we're getting lower.

784
00:49:20,440 --> 00:49:23,080
因为我要降落
That's what happens when I land.

785
00:49:23,110 --> 00:49:24,410
为什么
Why are we landing?

786
00:49:24,440 --> 00:49:28,290
这显然是它住的洞穴
Because this is the cove that he obviously lives in.

787
00:49:28,320 --> 00:49:30,290
你干嘛降落?
So why are we landing?

788
00:49:31,160 --> 00:49:32,340
赫克托
Hector!

789
00:49:41,540 --> 00:49:43,100
可以拓下来吗
We can lift it?

790
00:49:43,130 --> 00:49:44,480
也许可以
Maybe.

791
00:49:44,510 --> 00:49:46,100
别把它弄糊
Don't want to mush it there.

792
00:49:46,130 --> 00:49:47,440
才没有
I'm not mushing it.

793
00:49:47,470 --> 00:49:50,770
别那么用力 太软了
You might mush it. It's a little soft.

